# TradeRefer â€” Guided Product Tour Implementation Spec

**Library:** NextStep (`nextstepjs`)
**Date:** March 2026
**Version:** 1.0

> This document contains everything you need to implement guided product tours for both the Referrer Dashboard and Business Dashboard on TradeRefer. All code is copy-paste ready.

---

## 1. Install

```bash
npm install nextstepjs motion
```

No changes to `tailwind.config.ts` or `next.config.ts` are required.

---

## 2. Files to Create

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `components/tour/TourCard.tsx` | Custom branded tour popover card |
| `components/tour/HelpButton.tsx` | Floating `?` button fixed to bottom-right |
| `tours/referrer-tours.ts` | All tour steps for the Referrer Dashboard |
| `tours/business-tours.ts` | All tour steps for the Business Dashboard |

**Existing files to modify:**
- `app/layout.tsx` â€” wrap with `NextStepProvider` + `NextStep`
- `app/dashboard/referrer/layout.tsx` â€” add `<HelpButton tourName="referrer-main" />`
- `app/dashboard/business/layout.tsx` â€” add `<HelpButton tourName="business-main" />`
- Multiple page/component files â€” add `id` attributes to target elements (see Section 5)

---

## 3. Update app/layout.tsx

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import { NextStepProvider, NextStep } from 'nextstepjs';
import { referrerTours } from '@/tours/referrer-tours';
import { businessTours } from '@/tours/business-tours';
import { TourCard } from '@/components/tour/TourCard';

const allTours = [...referrerTours, ...businessTours];

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <NextStepProvider>
          <NextStep
            steps={allTours}
            cardComponent={TourCard}
            showNextStepBackdrop={true}
          >
            {children}
          </NextStep>
        </NextStepProvider>
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

> **Note:** If the app already has `ClerkProvider`, `ThemeProvider`, or other providers in `layout.tsx`, keep them. Nest `NextStepProvider` inside those existing providers, just wrapping `children`.

